# Architecture Principles

## Core principles

- **Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)**: One clear purpose per module/component.
- **Explicit dependency boundaries**: Dependencies flow in one direction; no circular imports.
- **No business logic inside UI components**: Keep components declarative; put logic in hooks, services, or utils.
- **Prefer composition over inheritance**: Compose small components and hooks; avoid class hierarchies.
- **Pure functions where possible**: Same inputs → same outputs; side effects only in dedicated layers (hooks, API layer).

## Project structure (current)

```
src/
  app/              # router.tsx (routes), providers.tsx (Auth + Router)
  components/       # UI components in subfolders
    ui/              # AuthImage (generic)
    auth/            # Login, AuthGuard
    modals/          # All *Modal components
    workflows/       # WorkflowList, WorkflowDetail, WorkflowCreate, NodeManager, NodeParserEditor
    settings/       # Settings
    dashboard/       # Dashboard
    activity/       # Activity
  features/         # feature-based public API (index.ts re-exports)
    auth/           # AuthProvider, useAuth, Login, AuthGuard, clearStoredAuth
    workflows/      # WorkflowList, WorkflowDetail, WorkflowCreate, useWorkflows
    settings/       # Settings
    activity/       # Activity
    dashboard/      # Dashboard
  hooks/            # shared hooks (useWorkflows, useServerHealthCheck)
  services/
    api/            # workflows, servers, stats (HTTP layer)
  lib/              # shared helpers
  types/            # shared types (index.ts)
  utils/            # auth, settings, imageCompression
```

- **Feature-based**: Each feature is self-contained (components, hooks, services, types).
- **No cross-feature imports** except via shared services or `lib/`.
- **UI components** in `components/ui`; **business logic** in `features/*/services` or `services/api`.

## Boundaries

- **No circular imports**: Dependencies must form a DAG. Use dependency inversion (e.g. callbacks, interfaces) if needed.
- **Absolute imports**: Use path alias (e.g. `@/`) configured in Vite/tsconfig; avoid deep relative paths.
- **Typed API contracts**: Prefer shared types/schemas with backend; validate responses (e.g. Zod).
